### Project Overview

This project aims to create a simple 3D chess game in C++. The game will feature a 3D chessboard with pieces that can be moved around. The game will also include basic AI opponents and a scoring system.

### Game Mechanics

* The game will be implemented using the OpenGL library for 3D rendering.
* The game will feature a 3D chessboard with 8x8 squares.
* Each player will have 16 pieces (king, queen, rook, bishop, knight, pawn).
* Pieces will be represented by 3D models.
* The game will include basic AI opponents (MinMax algorithm).
* The game will keep track of scores.

### Code Structure

The code will be organized into the following folders:

* `src`: contains the C++ source code.
* `res`: contains resources (3D models, textures, etc.).
* `doc`: contains documentation (README, user manual, etc.).

